## ELA & Math Growth Scores

Next we look at the growth scores for ELA and Math. The first thing to notice about these graphs is that all the predictors converge to zero much faster than the previous two graphs. We can tell this by looking at the absolute numbers on the X axis. On the first two graphs it took until around 0.1 - 0.15 penalty for all predictors to reach zero. In these graphs it takes a much smaller penalty (roughly 0.01 - 0.03) for all predictors to reach zero significance. This tells us that none of the predictors are as significant as the previous graphs. However, there are some marginally significant predictors. Namely the ones seen previously as well as two new categories for grades served by the school.


